  id: Ulna_R
  partName: Ulna Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right ulna is a long bone positioned along the lateral side of the canine
    forearm and extends from the elbow to the wrist region. It forms an important
    part of the elbow joint through the olecranon process,
  - which serves as the attachment site for the triceps muscle responsible for elbow
    extension. Although the radius bears most body weight, the ulna contributes significantly
    to joint stability and forelimb mechanics. It also provides attachment areas
    for muscles controlling paw and forearm movement.
